Leptospirosis - Palau 2000.2811
Date: Sun, 2 Jul 2000 07:04:51 -0300
From: Paul Levett <levett@sunbeach.net

The posting on leptospirosis in Palau is incorrect in stating that the
indirect hemagglutination assay detects leptospiral IgM. It actually
detects both IgG and IgM, as do other agglutination tests. ELISA-based
specific IgM assays could confirm the diagnosis sooner, as they become
positive earlier in the course of illness than IHA.
--
Paul N. Levett, PhD ABMM FCCM
Professor of Clinical Microbiology
University of the West Indies
School of Clinical Medicine & Research
Barbados
Leptospira Laboratory
