*****
[2
Date: Tue, 4 Jul 2000 09:17:00 +0900
From: Michele Pineda, MPH <epi.cure@palaunet.com>

Thank you for the clarification regarding leptospirosis serology. Indeed
both IgG and IgM class antibodies are detectable by the hemagglutination
assay.
We may be limited in Palau from performing the leptospirosis ELISA because
of lack of instrumentation (specifically, a spectrophotometer). Information
regarding a rapid assay for leptospirosal IgM that would be suitable under
these circumstances would be greatly appreciated.
--
Michele Pineda, MPH
Epidemiologist
Ministry of Health
Republic of Palau
epi.cure@palaunet.com
